<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of cases of mumps on the island of Guam has increased to more
than a hundred from the 5 cases reported on 25 Mar 2010. Whereas the
original cases were mostly schoolchildren, the age range of the new cases
is not stated. Since Guam law requires all students entering school to
submit proof of immunization that includes 2 doses of the measles, mumps
and rubella (MMR) vaccine, it may be that the new cases are adults where
the consequences of mumps virus infection are more serious. Clarification
would be welcomed.

Guam is located in the western north Pacific Ocean, and is the largest and
southernmost island in the Mariana Islands archipelago. A map of Guam can
be accessed at
<http://www.picresorts.com/en/Guam/Background/Map-Of-Guam.jpg>. The
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Guam is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/01bB>. - Mod.CP]
